Ad Text:
Who is Alliance Airlines?

Alliance Airlines is Australasia’s leading provider of contract, wetlease charter and allied aviation and maintenance services. With a fleet of 79 aircraft and a workforce of over 1,500 employees, Alliance delivers essential aviation solutions to the mining, energy, and government sectors, as well as wet lease services to major carriers. Alliance is proud to be known as Australia’s leading FIFO charter operator with a history of delivering the highest standards of safety, reliability, and operational performance for some of the world largest mining houses. Alliance holds International Air Transport Association’s Operational Safety Audit certification, the only Australian contract and charter operator to do so and has gold status Basic Aviation Risk Standard (BARS), being the first such carrier in Australia to achieve gold status. Operating nationally throughout Australia, Alliance’s has bases in Brisbane, Rockhampton, Cairns, Townsville, Darwin, Perth and Adelaide. 

What's the role on offer?

Based at our Head Office near Brisbane Airport, this is an exciting opportunity to join our Procurement team as the Business Analyst – Procurement, reporting to the Head of Procurement and Part Sales. In this role, you will support data-driven decision-making, enhance procurement efficiency, and drive continuous improvement across key business processes.

You will be responsible for:

Mapping and documenting existing procurement, demand, and material management workflows.
Identifying process inefficiencies and designing improved future-state workflows.
Leading or supporting automation and digitisation projects across procurement systems.
Developing KPIs, dashboards, and analytical reports to monitor performance.
Consolidating and maintaining departmental process documentation and training materials.
Driving continuous improvement and supporting cultural change toward data-driven operations.

What’s in it for me?

Novated Leasing for Employees – This enables you to bundle all your car running costs into one regular ongoing tax effective payment! Get more money in your back pocket!
Salary Packaging – Another option to get more money into your back pocket!
Discounted Qantas Club memberships!
Discounted tickets to REDS (QRU) Games and merchandise!
Discounted Hotels, Tours and Cruises - Qualify for discounts on just about every type of vacation you can imagine!

Who we are looking for:

Our ideal candidate will bring experience in procurement, supply chain, data analytics, aviation, or related industries. You will be analytical, proactive, and ready to contribute to the ongoing growth and transformation of Alliance Airlines.

Your skills and experience:

Tertiary qualifications in Business, Supply Chain, Data Analytics, or a related field.
Strong understanding of procurement, supply chain processes, and data analysis.
Demonstrated ability to analyse large data sets and provide meaningful insights.
Experience supporting process improvements, workflow mapping, or system integration.
Effective communication and stakeholder engagement skills across technical and non-technical groups.
Ability to work both autonomously and collaboratively in a fast-paced environment.

Does this sound like you?

If the sound of this role excites you and you have the skills, we're looking for we'd love to hear from you. Hit that Apply button and Ash will speak to you shortly.

At Alliance Airlines we value diversity, equality and inclusion, we are committed to providing working environments where everyone is included and treated fairly and with respect.

We encourage people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander descent and people from diverse backgrounds to apply.

All candidates must have full working rights within Australia, only candidates with a right to work in Australia will be considered.

We're supporting a financial services organisation undergoing a major finance platform uplift. They're looking for an experienced Data Migration Lead to take ownership of converting 15+ months of legacy financial transactions from legacy systems into a new finance data model.

If you enjoy solving complex data challenges, working hands-on, and seeing your work land directly in an ERP environment, this is a great opportunity.

The role:

You'll lead the end-to-end migration of historical financial data from a legacy system into a new finance platform. Your focus is on extracting and transforming data from the old platform and preparing it in the exact format the ERP vendor needs to load into the new system. This includes:

Extracting financial data from SQL Server

Designing and delivering detailed data mapping between legacy GL and the new chart of accounts

Building and refining transformation logic (splits, reclassifications, worktags/dimensions)

Producing structured Excel load files in the vendor’s templates, which the ERP team will then load into the new platform

Running trial conversions and validating data with accountants

Ensuring balances reconcile correctly post-conversion

Working closely with the project manager, finance teams, system admins and technical leads

This is a hands-on role ideal for someone who loves turning messy data into clean, usable structures.


Your experience:

We're looking for someone who can confidently own the migration stream.

Must have:

Strong SQL experience (SQL Server preferred)

Advanced Excel skills (lookups, pivots, complex formulas)

Proven experience converting legacy financial data (GL, journals, cost centres) into a new data model

Experience in at least one ERP or finance system migration (Workday, SAP, Oracle, Dynamics, etc.)

Ability to design and execute data mapping and transformation logic

Comfortable working independently with support from a project team

Nice to have:

Exposure to TM1 or finance modelling tools

Prior experience producing ERP load files


What's in it for you?

Possible to start immediately before Christmas

Work directly with a high-calibre project lead

Full ownership of a business-critical workstream

Flexibility on contract arrangement and work arrangements

Clear scope, clear milestones, and immediate impact


How to apply

If you have hands-on finance data migration experience and enjoy solving complex transformation challenges, I'd love to speak with you.

Please apply via Seek or contact Kathrin Pantenburg at Kohort Partners on LinkedIn for a confidential discussion.

This organisation is looking for a Change Analyst (CA) to assist in managing change and communications across multiple IT projects and stakeholder groups including external agencies such as QLD Police Service and QLD Revenue Office.

The scope includes replacing multiple legacy IT systems that support camera detected offence processing, along with implementing new applications to support camera planning and scheduling, and data analytics and reporting services.

The CA will work closely with the Organisational Change Manager (OCM) and Program Manager at the program level, along with project managers, project team members, SMEs and key stakeholders, to assist in managing change related to each project.

A variety of communication channels, training interventions, and tools will be used to ensure stakeholders are engaged and supported through the change and have the tools and capability to be successful in adopting the new systems and processes.

The CA will be required to:
• Support the Organisational Change Manager to implement change plans and activities to support adoption of the new systems and processes delivered across the program
• Conduct and document change impact assessments, considering the impacts related to business process, organisational structure, roles and responsibilities, culture, tools, and technologies.
• Develop and deliver broad and targeted communications across multiple channels to effectively communicate change related information to internal and external stakeholders.
• Meet regularly with stakeholders (particularly end users) to assess change readiness and understand concerns, provide support, and seek feedback on how change can be implemented effectively based on user needs.
• Contribute to the design of training and support materials and participate in training related activities to build knowledge and capability.
• Support go-live activities and provide post rollout support and coaching and monitor adoption.

Skills Required
• High level experience in designing and implementing change initiatives to achieve project/program outcomes, particularly on IT centric modernisation projects.
• High level experience in stakeholder engagement, particularly end users of systems including management staff, and building relationships to support and lead people through change.
• Significant experience in assessing the impacts of a change initiative for specific teams and roles based on business process, technology, culture, and role responsibilities.
• Significant experience in designing and implementing communication plans to meet program/project and stakeholder needs including use of social media, internal web sites (such as sharepoint), other electronic media, collaboration tools, and print.
• Significant experience in designing and delivering training/support activities for (and guiding people through) the transition to new ways of working and adopting new systems and processes.

The following attributes are mandatory:
• 8+ years’ experience in change and communications management working on large projects or programs of work related to IT systems.

The following attributes are highly desirable:
• Certification in Change Management (e.g., PROSCI, APMG) and/or tertiary studies related to organisational change
• Bachelor’s degree in business, Psychology, HR, or related field

Salary: No contractor fees / two pay runs per week

Central Forecasting Team

Treasury is looking for talented, team-oriented, and highly motivated staff to fill positions in the Central Forecasting Team of the Macroeconomic Conditions and Population Division (MCPD). 

Treasury’s Central Forecasting Team (CFT) produces the economic forecasts and projections that underpin the Australian Government’s economic narrative, working with teams across MCPD and Treasury. This is a great opportunity lead the team that drives the production of the Government’s official macroeconomic forecasts, help frame the macroeconomic narrative, and support government decision making.

About the Roles

The Directors of CFT leads a talented and driven team that also develops and maintains the forecasting infrastructure, and the delivers several projects aimed at improving Treasury’s analytical frameworks and forecasts. The role requires significant experience with modelling, having a well-developed macroeconomic framework and coding capabilities. This position demands exceptional capability to lead, deliver, and innovate in a fast-moving and complex environment. The successful candidate will co lead the forecasting team to drive the team’s performance, development and wellbeing.

The role requires excellent conceptual and analytical skills, and a capacity to communicate clearly to a variety of audiences. Specific responsibilities include:

Managing forecasting processes within the Macroeconomic Conditions and Population Division.
Maintaining and further developing Treasury’s forecasting frameworks and infrastructure.
Building the modelling and forecasting capabilities of staff across the Division.
Leading the timely delivery of influential analysis to brief the Treasurer and Senior Treasury Executives on macroeconomic developments and policy settings.
Supporting the delivery of a pipeline of strategic projects across the Division. 

The successful applicant will have demonstrated experience:

Applying macroeconomic theory and frameworks, including working with macroeconometric models, preparing macroeconomic forecasts and exercising professional judgement.
Leading a team of people and building technical capability.
Communicating clearly and succinctly to influence a broad range of stakeholders.
Operating in a dynamic setting as a team player, working productively across the Division and the Department and exercising sound judgement. 

Desirable Qualifications / Experience

Tertiary qualification(s) in a relevant field, including, but not limited to, economics, econometrics, mathematics, or public policy.
Ideally, we are looking for candidates with at least eight years of relevant work experience.

Experience in one or more of the following will be particularly well-regarded: 

Applied economic research and analysis
Government policy development and assessment
Relevant private-sector experience.
